HEADWORD: Saw-whet
<hw>Saw"-whet`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small North American owl (<spn>Nyctale Acadica</spn>), destitute
of ear tufts and having feathered toes; -- called also <altname>Acadian
owl</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

